nt works as a capstone to the Becker oeuvre—not because the works are perfect, but because they offer an illuminating, instructive glimpse into the machinations of an economist who wasn’t motivated by publications. Here, and throughout his works, an inquisitive spirit remains remarkable and forever resonant.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomics. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aElias, Julio J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGlaeser, Edward L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlaeser, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMulligan, Casey B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMurphy, Kevin M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226827216423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226827216/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles